                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" source="#bib1074-1" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/authors">Peter Makhluf was a Maronite cleric, scholar, and author, who served as the
                        secretary for Patriarch Stephen al-Duwayhi and as bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/714">Cyrpus</placeName>. He travelled
                        frequently between <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/487">Lebanon</placeName>, where he was born, and <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/641">Rome</placeName> where he studied and
                        was involved in the printing, revision, and translation of the Maronite
                        breviary.</note>
